About Us


About First State Investments (Singapore)

First State Investments (Singapore) is part of Colonial First State Global Asset Management, the asset management business of the Commonwealth Bank of Australia, with investment offices in Sydney, London, Edinburgh, Singapore, Hong Kong and Jakarta. The group has funds under management of AUD 149.0 billion as of 31 December 2009, and provides asset management services to wholesale and institutional investors across a diverse range of asset classes. 
In Singapore, we provide a diversified range of products to both retail investors and institutions. The collective investment schemes offered to retail investors include global and regional funds, as well as specialist sector funds. These include award-winning funds such as First State Singapore Growth Fund, First State Regional China Fund and First State Asia Innovation Fund*.

* For a full listing of our awards, please refer to http://www.firststateasia.com/AwardsEnSG.aspx



Investment Approach

At First State Investments (Singapore), we are active, fundamental  investors. We aim to create wealth over the medium to long term by applying an  active and disciplined approach to investing in quality assets. We use a  'bottom-up' approach to stock selection, placing emphasis on high quality  proprietary research in addition to making direct contact with the companies in  which we invest. We focus on investing in companies with sustainable earnings  per share (EPS) growth, high quality attributes and sensible valuations.





