Media Release: First State Investments commits to increased quality of climate risk disclosure in latest Responsible Investment report
News | 12 May 2016
First State Investments (First State) has today published its ninth annual Responsible Investment & Stewardship Report, in which it further enhances its reporting on environmental, social and governance (ESG) issues, including disclosing its climate risk exposures across a number of asset classes for the first time.







Making the case for responsible investment
News | 28 May 2014
First State business leaders work with the University of Cambridge Institute for Sustainability Leadership (CISL) to make the case for Responsible investment. In their new report the CISL warns that today’s economy continues to draw down on the world’s natural capital rather than living off its interest and  identifies a need for strong and collective leadership from the Investment industry, arguing there is a “moral, financial and economic case for action”.







First State launches stewardship principles
News | 3 Dec, 2013
First State Investments announced today that it has published a set of Global Stewardship Principles for adoption across its business that will be compliant with the current disclosure requirements of the UK and other stewardship codes.







First State strengthens its foothold in Europe
News | September 2012
First State Investments (“FSI”) has today announced the opening of a representative office in Frankfurt am Main and a senior appointment within the business, as it continues its expansion in continental Europe.







First State Investments strengthens Property Securities Team
News | August 2012
First State Investments („FSI‟) has today announced changes to the Listed Property Securities team. Stephen Hayes has been appointed to the role of Head of Property Securities, based in Sydney. 







Global Resources Team appoints Senior Analyst
News | July 2012
First State Investments (FSI) has today announced the appointment of Mr. Peter Mangano as a Senior Analyst within the Global Resources team. Peter will be based in Sydney office and commences his role today.





